{"title":"Gideon’s Rivendell Atlantis: You Had Me at Pineapple Bob – Gideon Tsang","link":"https://theradavist.com/gideons-rivendell-atlantis/","date":1730980829000,"content":"<p><em>Gideon Tsang has spent the better part of his life admiring and collecting bicycles designed by Grant Petersen. From early Bridgestones to current Rivendells, the bicycles designed around Grant’s ethos of moving mindfully and enjoying the ride have always resonated with Gideon. Enjoy this firsthand account about a bicycle collection that came and went, and the story behind Gideon’s dream bike: a rare 26″ Rivendell Atlantis 2.</em></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis24.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis24.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis24.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis24.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3>The Synergistic Combination: The Bridgestone Stable</h3>\n<p>The story starts in 2007 – a full decade since I had last touched my <a href=\"https://www.pinkbike.com/news/now-that-was-a-bike-bontrager-race-lite.html\" target=\"_blank\">Bontrager Race Lite</a>. My friend <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/eastsidepedalpushers/?hl=en\" target=\"_blank\">Lee</a> handed me an old <a href=\"https://www.sheldonbrown.com/bridgestone/index.html\">Bridgestone catalog</a>.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis18.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis18.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis18.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis18.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis66.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis66.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis66.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis66.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis19.png?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis19.png?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis19.png?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis19.png?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>The first page I turned to featured Pineapple Bob eating a banana, wearing a cycling cap, riding his Bridgestone RB-T with a musette over his shoulder. In the same catalog, I found Bob tucked into an aero position on an orange XO-1 with mustache bars. I was smitten at first sight.</p>\n<p>Over the next few years, I amassed an impressive Bridgestone collection, starting with an XO-1, which led to an RB-1, an MB-Zip, and, the hardest to hunt down at the time, Bob’s RB-T. By 2010 I had a solid Bridgestone stable. It was time to take the pilgrimage to visit Bridgestone’s offspring, <a href=\"https://rivbike.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Rivendell Bicycle Works</a>.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis20.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis20.jpg?w=200&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis20.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis21.png?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis21.png?w=200&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis21.png?w=600&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis17.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis17.jpg?w=200&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis17.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis22.png?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis22.png?w=200&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis22.png?w=600&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3>The Wizard of Riv</h3>\n<p>I flew from Austin to California and hopped on a train from San Francisco to Walnut Creek, where I took my MB-Zip off the bike hook. As I mounted my Zip, a beautiful blue bike with a front basket and a large saddlebag zoomed past me. It was the wizard himself, <a href=\"https://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2024/09/23/the-art-of-taking-it-slow\" target=\"_blank\">Grant Petersen</a>.</p>\n<p>I finally caught up with the wizard as he arrived at his warehouse. Grant was kind and generous with his time. They were building a darkroom in the back of the Rivendell warehouse and he showed me around. He recognized my name from Flickr and gave me my first in-person photography critique: “I can’t tell if you’re a really good photographer or a really bad one.” Fair enough – like anyone starting out, my photography ratio was more bad than good.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis2.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis2.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis2.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis2.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis1.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis1.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis1.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis1.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>He set me up on a Bombadil with a map secured to the stem with a magnet and told me to come back before they closed.</p>\n<p>A couple of hours later, I returned with a big smile on my face, told him I loved his work, and proudly relayed that I owned four Bridgestones. With a mischievous smirk, he said, “Why? One Rivendell is better than four Bridgestones.”</p>\n<p>I hopped back on my MB-Zip and headed to the train station. Am I a bad photographer or a good one? Is one Rivendell better than four Bridgestones?</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis6.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis6.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis6.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis6.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis5.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis5.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis5.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis5.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis4.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis4.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis4.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis4.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis3.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis3.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis3.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis3.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis7.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis7.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis7.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis7.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis8.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis8.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis8.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis8.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3>Grant’s Greatest Hits</h3>\n<p>Later that year, I bought my first Rivendell frameset – a custom-painted <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/rivendell-rambouillet-road-bike/\" target=\"_blank\">Rambouillet</a> with S &amp; S couplers.</p>\n<p>That Rambouillet is the only bike I regret letting go of. I’ve been trying to find those <a href=\"https://analogcycles.com/products/copy-of-specialites-ta-carmina-crankset-complete-94-bcd-double\" target=\"_blank\">Spécialités TA Carmina Cranks</a> for the last five years.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis9.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis9.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis9.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis9.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis11.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis11.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis11.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis11.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>In 2014, my Sam Hillborne was born. That was my gateway to the fine pairing of the legendary <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LDMk-W6QDrw&amp;t=321s\" target=\"_blank\">Campy 10-speed Ergopower with 8-speed Shimano</a> hack.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis14.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis14.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis14.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis14.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis15.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis15.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis15.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis15.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis13.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis13.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis13.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis13.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>In 2016 I acquired a Hunqapillar. I had desired such a bike since I felt the magic of the Bombadil six years earlier. My Hunq became my go-to touring and bikepacking horse.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis16.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis16.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis16.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis16.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis12.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis12.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis12.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis12.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis10.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis10.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis10.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis10.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3>Finding Atlantis</h3>\n<p>In 2022, I sold my entire stable (<em>gasp!</em>) to travel the world. Upon returning, it was a no-brainer that if I had just one bike, it would be an Atlantis. I prefer the shorter chainstays of the earlier models and, in particular, wanted the 26” Atlantis 2 with the larger clearance. After quite a bit of searching, I finally found one in New Haven, CT.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis62.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis62.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis62.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis62.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis64.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis64.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis64.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis64.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis61.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis61.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis61.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis61.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>As much as I love the Atlantis, the greenish-blue color of the inside of a Russian submarine wasn’t part of my earth-toned palette preference. I got in touch with <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=m1PToF_mkSY\" target=\"_blank\">Rick Stefani</a>, a painter and friend of Rivendell in San Francisco, and had it painted a dark metallic brown. Sorry, Grant!</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis26.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis26.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis26.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis26.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>I worked with <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/drosscycle/\" target=\"_blank\">David Ross</a> of <a href=\"https://themeteor.cafe/bike\" target=\"_blank\">Meteor Bikes</a> in Austin to craft a build around a 1X Shimano XTR 950 crankset, which required a custom chainring made in Poland by <a href=\"https://www.garbaruk.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Garbaruk</a>, along with a NOS XTR HP-M900 headset that David magically sourced.</p>\n<p>Ladies and gentlemen, I may not know if I’m a good or bad photographer, but I do know this: one Rivendell beats four Bridgestones any day. This is my Atlantis, photographed by <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/roszko/\" target=\"_blank\">Alex Roszko.</a></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis23.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis23.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis23.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis23.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis49.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis49.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis49.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis49.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis31.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis31.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis31.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis31.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis42.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis42.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis42.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/10/Gideons-Rivendell-Atlantis42.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>Build list:</p>\n<p>Frame and fork: Rivendell Atlantis 2<br />\nCrankset: Shimano XTR M950<br />\nChainring: Garbaruk XTR M950, 36T<br />\nRear Derailleur: Shimano XTR RD-M9000<br />\nCassette: Shimano XTR M9001 11-Speed 11-40t<br />\nHeadset: Shimano XTR HP-M900<br />\nLevers: Paul Love Lever<br />\nBrakes: Paul Motolite<br />\nWheels: Crust 26” All Nighter<br />\nTires: Ultradynamico Mars Race, 26” x 2.2”<br />\nBars: Nitto Albatross<br />\nGrips: Brooks Ergonomic Rubber Grip<br />\nSaddle: Brooks Cambium Saddle<br />\nPedals: White Industries urban platform pedals<br />\nSeatpost: Nitto S65 Seatpost<br />\nStem: Nitto Crystem 3 Stem, 120 mm<br />\nQuick release skewers: Paul Components<br />\nBottle Cages: Nitto R</p>\n<p><em>A lovely build for a lovely human. Learn more about Rivendell <a href=\"https://www.rivbike.com\">at their website</a>, and be sure to read <a href=\"https://www.rivbike.com/blogs/grant-petersens-blog\">Grant’s Blahg</a>.</em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/gideons-rivendell-atlantis/\">Gideon’s Rivendell Atlantis: You Had Me at Pineapple Bob</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"Josh Weinberg","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"7a68d01d650072e83424b3964132783fa0e2e43e89813005a2cc9192b3543400","category":"Cycling"}